item.title: Silab commands
item.dc:creator: @Java_Is_My_Bitch Java Is My Bitch™
item.description:
@Java_Is_My_Bitch wrote:

[quote=“webbsta, post:7, topic:165332”]Too many brackets open, you need as many open brackets as you have closed or vice versa, here is what you need:

else if (command.startsWith("command Name") && playerRights >= 0)
{
addItem(Item ID, How many You want them to get);
}

any brackets before sentences like that will belong to another snippet of code, i always find it helpful to count how many open brackets are after the “else if” or “if” and then when theres a close bracket, then take away a bracket you just counted, it helps you keep track of them so you can find any brackets you may have added or not added by accident.[/quote]

Lol Stalker thats what i do. Or just count you have to have an even Number of brackets open or closed, count them all and if you an even number, your good, odd number, just add one till its even.

[quote=“xx qwertyuiop xx, post:6, topic:165332”]I’m anti-silab as well.
People make too big a deal of that shit.[/quote]

Yeah seriously i don’t find it that awesome.
